Dialogue: 0,0:00:01.85,0:00:03.31,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Two of them twenty years ago...
Dialogue: 0,0:00:03.85,0:00:07.31,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,And one fifteen years ago, became victims of the serial murderer.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:08.02,0:00:09.53,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,It was then that that the criminal...
Dialogue: 0,0:00:09.53,0:00:13.28,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Ran down Superintendent Morimura with his car and killed him.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:14.03,0:00:17.78,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Superintendent Matsumoto in turn followed him,\Nand ended up with a scar over his left eye.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:19.16,0:00:21.95,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,For the cases twenty years ago, their respective statutes have passed.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:22.54,0:00:24.21,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,But for the case from 15 years ago...
Dialogue: 0,0:00:24.21,0:00:26.54,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,There are still three days until the time runs out.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:27.50,0:00:29.80,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,There are two clues that connect the criminal.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:30.17,0:00:34.93,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,The first: A scar on the culprit's back\Ncourtesy of Superintendent Matsumoto.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:35.68,0:00:37.39,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,The other: Whistling.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:38.01,0:00:40.18,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,A song that was popular twenty years ago...
Dialogue: 0,0:00:40.18,0:00:42.18,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,He was always whistling it.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:43.35,0:00:46.40,Dialogue Top,,0,0,0,,As Detective Takagi and the others carried out their investigation...
Dialogue: 0,0:00:45.60,0:00:48.73,Character Card,,0,0,0,,Hiramune Douji (41)\NCriminal Psychologist
Dialogue: 0,0:00:46.48,0:00:48.73,Dialogue Top,,0,0,0,,A criminologist by the name of Hiramune Douji{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r}...
Dialogue: 0,0:00:49.32,0:00:54.11,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Appeared on TV and repeatedly provoked the\Ncriminal as he had in magazines before.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:54.61,0:00:55.57,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,And then...
Dialogue: 0,0:00:56.20,0:00:58.95,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,We happened to pass a strange man near the entrance.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:59.91,0:01:03.79,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,It was a man who was whistling and wearing an off-season long coat.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:05.79,0:01:06.87,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Could it be...
Dialogue: 0,0:01:06.87,0:01:08.13,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,He actually came here!?
Dialogue: 0,0:01:08.63,0:01:10.04,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,The serial killer!
Dialogue: 0,0:01:12.34,0:01:14.47,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Love is eternal, labyrinths are mysterious.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:14.51,0:01:16.05,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Saturday nights are for mystery!
Dialogue: 0,0:01:16.76,0:01:18.68,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Something is different about Detective Takagi!
Dialogue: 0,0:01:18.76,0:01:20.51,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Will it be a straight line to arrest the culprit!?
Dialogue: 0,0:01:20.89,0:01:22.52,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Perceiving the one and only truth...
Dialogue: 0,0:01:22.52,0:01:24.39,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,The appearance of a child and the intellect of an adult.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:24.39,0:01:26.10,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,His name is: Detective Conan!
Dialogue: 0,0:03:14.34,0:03:15.46,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Seriously, Conan{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-kun{\r}!?
Dialogue: 0,0:03:15.79,0:03:17.30,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,You're saying that, at that apartment building...
Dialogue: 0,0:03:17.30,0:03:20.22,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,It's highly likely that the serial killer appeared!?
Dialogue: 0,0:03:20.38,0:03:21.13,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Right!
Dialogue: 0,0:03:21.13,0:03:24.93,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,That criminal psychologist, Hiramune{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r},\Njust ridiculed the serial killer on TV...
Dialogue: 0,0:03:24.05,0:03:29.68,Signs,,0,0,0,,Hiramune
Dialogue: 0,0:03:24.93,0:03:26.47,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,So he may have come to his apartment!
Dialogue: 0,0:03:27.51,0:03:30.02,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Regardless, I'm going to check out his room!
Dialogue: 0,0:03:30.98,0:03:32.39,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Wait, Conan{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-kun{\r}!
Dialogue: 0,0:03:32.39,0:03:33.06,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Conan{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-kun{\r}!?
Dialogue: 0,0:03:33.81,0:03:35.69,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Chiba{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-kun{\r}, ready the car!
Dialogue: 0,0:03:35.69,0:03:36.27,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Yes!
Dialogue: 0,0:03:36.27,0:03:39.07,Signs,,0,0,0,,Hiramune
Dialogue: 0,0:03:42.57,0:03:43.74,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,That's strange...
Dialogue: 0,0:03:50.87,0:03:51.87,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,It's unlocked...
Dialogue: 0,0:03:57.29,0:03:58.67,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Hiramune{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r}?
Dialogue: 0,0:03:58.67,0:03:59.67,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Are you here?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:03.09,0:04:03.63,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Hiramune-sa—
Dialogue: 0,0:04:06.10,0:04:07.10,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Hiramune{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r}!
Dialogue: 0,0:04:10.68,0:04:11.48,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,It's no use.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:13.77,0:04:14.69,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,This is...
Dialogue: 0,0:04:15.85,0:04:17.06,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Could this be...
Dialogue: 0,0:04:17.98,0:04:19.53,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,It's a Z...
Dialogue: 0,0:04:21.28,0:04:25.20,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,The victim is the criminal psychologist, Hiramune Douji{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r}...
Dialogue: 0,0:04:25.20,0:04:25.74,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Age 41.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:26.66,0:04:29.45,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,The murder weapon was a fruit knife from the kitchen.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:29.99,0:04:32.96,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Judging by the stun-gun markings on his neck...
Dialogue: 0,0:04:33.37,0:04:36.67,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,As well as the alphabet letter carved into his back...
Dialogue: 0,0:04:37.17,0:04:37.92,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Most likely, this was...
Dialogue: 0,0:04:38.71,0:04:42.21,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,The work of the serial killer.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:43.84,0:04:46.26,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,But this time, the letter is a Z.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:46.80,0:04:49.56,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I completely expected an N this time.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:50.18,0:04:52.10,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Judging by the investigation reports...
Dialogue: 0,0:04:52.10,0:04:55.35,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,The letters carved on the previous victims were...
Dialogue: 0,0:04:55.35,0:04:58.56,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,E S W —\hin that order.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:59.40,0:05:02.48,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Should it have been an N this time, we\Nwould have east/west and south/north.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:03.19,0:05:13.04,Signs,,0,0,0,,Touzai (East/West)\NNanboku (South/North)
Dialogue: 0,0:05:03.19,0:05:04.07,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Huh?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:04.07,0:05:05.74,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,If it's Touzai Nanboku...
Dialogue: 0,0:05:05.90,0:05:09.07,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,That's East, West, South, North...
Dialogue: 0,0:05:09.58,0:05:13.00,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,E W S N, huh?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:13.37,0:05:16.37,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Well, we can be sure it wasn't a copycat.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:16.96,0:05:21.88,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,That is, since the culprit cutting letters into the\Nbodies of his victims was never made public.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:21.88,0:05:27.05,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,And it seems Conan{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-kun{\r}'s friends passed by the\Nman as he was whistling near the entrance, right?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:27.43,0:05:29.89,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,But, with only knowing this much...
Dialogue: 0,0:05:30.39,0:05:33.18,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,After you heard your friends mention a man that was whistling...
Dialogue: 0,0:05:33.77,0:05:35.52,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,You remembered him ridiculing the culprit on TV...
Dialogue: 0,0:05:35.52,0:05:39.23,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,And then thought Hiramune{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r} might be in danger...
Dialogue: 0,0:05:39.23,0:05:41.15,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Which caused you to rush over here.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:42.07,0:05:45.07,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,You're as attentive as a police detective...
Dialogue: 0,0:05:45.07,0:05:45.94,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Conan{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-kun{\r}.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:47.65,0:05:49.66,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,But, what he said...
Dialogue: 0,0:05:49.66,0:05:51.33,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Was it really that provoking?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:51.74,0:05:52.16,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Yes.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:52.87,0:05:56.87,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,"The suspect is likely trembling in bed,\Nwaiting for the deadline to pass."
Dialogue: 0,0:05:57.29,0:05:59.58,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,"In the event that isn't the case, come kill me."
Dialogue: 0,0:06:00.38,0:06:02.13,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Isn't that a challenge?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:02.13,0:06:02.67,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Yeah.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:03.38,0:06:08.26,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Hiramune{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r} was known for this style\Nof writing in newspapers and weeklies.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:08.55,0:06:13.81,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,It seems Hiramune{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r} immediately left the TV studio\Nafter his appearance at 4:00, and hurried home.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:14.39,0:06:17.14,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,In fact, he said he was going to meet an acquaintance.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:17.89,0:06:20.73,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,It's very likely that this acquaintance is the suspect.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:21.02,0:06:22.40,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Maybe...
Dialogue: 0,0:06:22.40,0:06:24.65,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,That certain someone is related to a copy machine?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:25.69,0:06:29.03,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Look, underneath Hiramune{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r}'s left hand.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:29.78,0:06:33.53,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,The Ctrl and C keys are stained with blood.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:34.16,0:06:37.29,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,When you press those two keys together, don't you get "copy"?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:38.62,0:06:39.79,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,That's true, but...
Dialogue: 0,0:06:40.37,0:06:43.67,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,It could have been left deliberately by the criminal.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:43.67,0:06:47.17,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,But still, there's no blood on his left hand, right?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:47.97,0:06:48.80,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,True...
Dialogue: 0,0:06:49.17,0:06:53.30,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Why is there just blood on his right hand that's grasping the mouse?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:53.64,0:06:54.76,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,That makes me think...
Dialogue: 0,0:06:54.76,0:06:57.10,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,He stained the keyboard with his bloody right hand...
Dialogue: 0,0:06:57.10,0:06:59.73,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,And then specially covered it with his left hand, you know?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:00.27,0:07:04.57,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,If the suspect had planned this, would he have done that as well?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:04.57,0:07:05.61,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,You're right.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:06.15,0:07:08.15,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,He would focus on making it more noticeable, huh?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:08.86,0:07:11.32,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Since his left hand wasn't covered in blood...
Dialogue: 0,0:07:11.32,0:07:13.41,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,We know he didn't end up staining the keys by chance while typing.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:14.07,0:07:16.49,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I guess that means he used his left hand to cover it...
Dialogue: 0,0:07:16.95,0:07:18.75,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Simply because he didn't want the suspect to notice?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:19.16,0:07:23.21,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,In other words, this—which was left by\NHiramune{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r} just as he was dying...
Dialogue: 0,0:07:23.96,0:07:26.09,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Amounts to a dying message.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:27.75,0:07:30.80,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,There also seems to be a copy machine in this room.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:30.80,0:07:33.64,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I inspected it earlier, but I didn't find anything out of the ordinary.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:34.60,0:07:36.68,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Could it be a copy band?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:37.26,0:07:41.98,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,The suspect was always whistling a song that\Nwas popular some twenty years ago, right?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:42.39,0:07:45.23,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Doesn't that mean he could know people from a copy band?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:45.23,0:07:47.36,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,There are many such bands.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:48.07,0:07:49.19,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Superintendent Matsumoto.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:49.19,0:07:50.36,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Superintendent!
Dialogue: 0,0:07:50.36,0:07:52.78,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,That means it could be a song that's popular all over the world, no?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:53.49,0:07:56.99,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Well, as for the serial killer...
Dialogue: 0,0:07:56.99,0:07:59.37,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,This melody holds some sort of deeper meaning.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:59.37,0:08:00.62,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Deeper meaning?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:01.04,0:08:03.33,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Immediately after that incident twenty years ago...
Dialogue: 0,0:08:03.33,0:08:07.88,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Morimura was questioning drivers of suspicious\Ncars that frequented the area of the crime scene.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:08.38,0:08:11.97,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,It was during the questioning that he was struck\Nby a car and killed in the line of duty, right?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:12.55,0:08:12.88,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Yes...
Dialogue: 0,0:08:13.38,0:08:16.30,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,When Morimura approached the car, he noticed that...
Dialogue: 0,0:08:16.30,0:08:18.35,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,The suspect was whistling at the time...
Dialogue: 0,0:08:19.26,0:08:21.39,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,While tears poured down his face.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:22.06,0:08:22.81,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Tears?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:23.73,0:08:24.31,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,All right!
Dialogue: 0,0:08:24.90,0:08:27.86,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Sato, Chiba —\hinquire around the neighborhood.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:27.86,0:08:28.48,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Yes, sir!
Dialogue: 0,0:08:28.73,0:08:33.90,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Shiratori, look into everyone related to Hiramune{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r}\Nagain, but with the clue of the copy machine in mind.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:33.90,0:08:34.82,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,That was my intention.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:35.16,0:08:39.83,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Takagi, just in case, visit the relatives of the previous three victims.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:39.83,0:08:42.50,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,See if they have any connection at all to Hiramune{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r}.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:42.50,0:08:43.54,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Understood?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:43.54,0:08:44.16,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Yes, sir!
Dialogue: 0,0:08:44.16,0:08:45.33,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I understand!
Dialogue: 0,0:08:47.67,0:08:49.71,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Well, he's enthusiastic.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:52.55,0:08:54.97,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Looks like my medicine has been more than effective, huh?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:57.43,0:09:00.18,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Only three days remain before the\Nstatute on the murder case is reached.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:00.89,0:09:04.98,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,But, if the criminal has committed a new offense,\Nthe statute will last another fifteen years!
Dialogue: 0,0:09:05.48,0:09:05.94,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Ah, no...
Dialogue: 0,0:09:06.73,0:09:09.27,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,The Code of Criminal Procedure was amended...
Dialogue: 0,0:09:09.27,0:09:12.82,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,The statute of limitations on murder cases\Nwas extended to twenty-five years!
Dialogue: 0,0:09:13.61,0:09:18.07,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,So long as I can catch the serial killer\Nwithin the next twenty-five years...
Dialogue: 0,0:09:20.78,0:09:22.66,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Sato{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r} and I can go to...
Dialogue: 0,0:09:23.58,0:09:25.00,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,The hot spring!
Dialogue: 0,0:09:26.54,0:09:27.83,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I see now.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:28.67,0:09:31.17,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,That would explain why you were more enthusiastic than usual.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:32.17,0:09:33.76,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Your motives are impure.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:33.76,0:09:35.38,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,A hot spring, that's great!
Dialogue: 0,0:09:35.38,0:09:37.76,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,You should take us with you!
Dialogue: 0,0:09:38.97,0:09:42.14,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,What are you all doing in my car!?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:42.97,0:09:45.98,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,You were the one who let us in back there.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:46.39,0:09:49.10,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,You asked us, "Where do you want to go?" in the parking lot...
Dialogue: 0,0:09:49.10,0:09:51.27,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,And opened the door without saying anything else.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:51.27,0:09:53.86,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,It didn't seem like you were really paying attention, though.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:56.28,0:10:01.66,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I was thinking about the hot sprin—I mean, I had the case in mind.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:01.66,0:10:02.20,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Well?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:02.20,0:10:03.24,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,What will you do?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:03.95,0:10:05.87,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Will you permit us to stay?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:06.50,0:10:07.54,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Or will we be dropped off?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:08.21,0:10:10.46,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Of course I'll be dropping you off!
Dialogue: 0,0:10:10.79,0:10:14.71,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,But, Ayumi{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-chan{\r} and Haibara{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r} saw the culprit, didn't they?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:15.55,0:10:16.63,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,But, see...
Dialogue: 0,0:10:16.63,0:10:21.22,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I'm just going to the homes of the relatives of the\Nvictims fifteen and twenty years ago right now.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:21.85,0:10:22.85,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,But you know...
Dialogue: 0,0:10:22.85,0:10:26.56,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,The family of the victims were all considered suspects as well.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:26.56,0:10:27.68,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Or so, that's what they said on TV.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:28.77,0:10:29.85,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,That's true, but...
Dialogue: 0,0:10:30.27,0:10:33.23,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Well, if this continues for another twenty-five years...
Dialogue: 0,0:10:33.23,0:10:38.65,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,And assuming Detective Sato is still waiting for you\Nas a 50 year-old woman with wrinkles on her face...
Dialogue: 0,0:10:39.07,0:10:40.36,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I guess you can try to do it all alone.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:41.57,0:10:42.87,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,So hollow...
Dialogue: 0,0:10:43.45,0:10:45.08,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,It will be fine if you do it now!
Dialogue: 0,0:10:45.08,0:10:46.50,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,She's still really beautiful!
Dialogue: 0,0:10:46.50,0:10:48.54,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Don't you think it's worth it?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:53.17,0:10:54.29,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,All right?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:54.29,0:10:55.96,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Only Conan{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-kun{\r} is conning with me.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:56.59,0:11:00.18,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,The rest of you need to wait patiently in the car, all right?
Dialogue: 0,0:11:00.18,0:11:01.18,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Yes!
Dialogue: 0,0:11:04.26,0:11:04.76,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Say...
Dialogue: 0,0:11:05.26,0:11:07.18,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,The one we're here to see...
Dialogue: 0,0:11:07.18,0:11:13.19,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,She's the widow of the doctor that was murdered\Ntwenty years ago, Boukawa Tsuguharu{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r}, right?
Dialogue: 0,0:11:13.48,0:11:14.61,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Yeah.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:14.61,0:11:17.61,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Boukawa{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r} was the clinic head of a large hospital.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:17.61,0:11:21.82,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Because his wife, Maiko{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r}, inherited a large fortune with his death...
Dialogue: 0,0:11:21.82,0:11:24.95,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,She became suspect and was called in for a number of line-ups.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:25.49,0:11:31.29,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Anyway, we had no proof, and since there was no\Nconnection to the second victim, Mugita{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r}...
Dialogue: 0,0:11:31.29,0:11:32.96,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,She remained only a suspect.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:36.04,0:11:37.34,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Yes...
Dialogue: 0,0:11:37.34,0:11:38.92,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I know this man.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:39.55,0:11:44.72,Dialogue Top,,0,0,0,,This is the criminal psychologist that seems\Nto always be on TV—Hiramune{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r}, right?
Dialogue: 0,0:11:40.55,0:11:46.93,Character Card,,0,0,0,,{\fad(250,0)}Boukawa Maiko (62)\NWife of Boukawa Tsuguharu
Dialogue: 0,0:11:44.89,0:11:46.93,Dialogue Top,,0,0,0,,What about him?
Dialogue: 0,0:11:47.18,0:11:50.68,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,He was found murdered in his apartment earlier.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:51.06,0:11:56.19,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,The one responsible is most likely the very same\Nperson that killed your husband twenty years ago.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:56.19,0:11:57.65,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,My, that's upsetting...
Dialogue: 0,0:11:58.07,0:12:04.57,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,As such, we've come to ask if your husband had\Nany sort of connection with Hiramune{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r}.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:04.91,0:12:06.16,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Well...
Dialogue: 0,0:12:06.16,0:12:08.37,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Just how old was this Hiramune{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r}?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:08.37,0:12:09.83,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,He was 41 years old.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:10.37,0:12:13.29,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Then, when my husband was killed twenty\Nyears ago, he would have only been 21.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:13.29,0:12:15.96,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,My husband was 50 years old when he died.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:16.46,0:12:20.38,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I can't imagine there's any link between them...
Dialogue: 0,0:12:20.38,0:12:22.09,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Is that so...
Dialogue: 0,0:12:22.09,0:12:24.89,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Are you sure he never met anyone in secret?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:26.18,0:12:28.47,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Who is this child?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:28.47,0:12:32.18,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I'm here to observe how policemen work for my social studies class!
Dialogue: 0,0:12:32.48,0:12:34.19,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Oh, is that so?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:35.35,0:12:41.23,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,But, it is true that he would often go out for\Ndrinks with someone on Saturday nights...
Dialogue: 0,0:12:41.23,0:12:43.57,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Do you have any idea who that was!?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:43.57,0:12:44.20,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,No...
Dialogue: 0,0:12:45.07,0:12:48.74,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,But once, when he returned home especially drunk, he said...
Dialogue: 0,0:12:49.08,0:12:54.12,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,"Damn! Wouldn't stop with the 'crybaby,\Ncrybaby,' making me out to be an idiot!"
Dialogue: 0,0:12:54.12,0:12:56.63,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,He said something along those lines.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:57.63,0:13:01.30,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,It was probably an old friend my husband knew from his childhood.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:01.67,0:13:06.30,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I told all of this to the police twenty years ago, though...
Dialogue: 0,0:13:08.97,0:13:11.81,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,The relative we're visiting next is for\Nthe second victim twenty years ago.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:12.14,0:13:14.68,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Murdered just two days after Boukawa{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r}...
Dialogue: 0,0:13:14.68,0:13:18.94,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,We'll see the younger brother of that associate professor\Nof science and engineering, Mugita Atsunori{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r}.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:19.27,0:13:23.19,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,As beneficiary in his brother's sizable life insurance\Npolicy, he was also considered a suspect, but...
Dialogue: 0,0:13:23.86,0:13:28.49,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Just like with the wife of the first victim,\Nthere was no connection between them.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:28.78,0:13:31.37,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,What about the third victim, Nabei{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r}?
Dialogue: 0,0:13:31.37,0:13:33.70,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Of course, there was no connection found there either.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:39.13,0:13:42.84,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,This is a criminal psychologist named Hiramune Douji{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r}, you say?
Dialogue: 0,0:13:42.96,0:13:46.97,Dialogue Top,,0,0,0,,No matter how many talk shows the guy has been on...
Dialogue: 0,0:13:43.96,0:13:49.55,Character Card,,0,0,0,,{\fad(250,0)}Mugita Hidekuni (56)\NYounger Brother Of Mugita Atsunori
Dialogue: 0,0:13:47.01,0:13:49.55,Dialogue Top,,0,0,0,,It doesn't change the fact that I dislike TV, you understand.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:50.22,0:13:53.18,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Well, Hiramune{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r} has been murdered.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:53.18,0:13:56.18,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,We're confident it was the same one who\Nmurdered your brother, Atsunori{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r}.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:57.60,0:13:58.69,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Aren't you surprised?
Dialogue: 0,0:13:58.98,0:14:00.69,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Yeah, well...
Dialogue: 0,0:14:01.19,0:14:05.53,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,After the statute on his case expired five years ago...
Dialogue: 0,0:14:05.53,0:14:07.74,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I'm afraid I decided to forget about it.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:08.15,0:14:10.16,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Then, well...
Dialogue: 0,0:14:10.16,0:14:13.49,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Is it possible your brother and Hiramune{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r} knew one another?
Dialogue: 0,0:14:13.87,0:14:15.00,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Who knows...
Dialogue: 0,0:14:15.00,0:14:16.50,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I don't think so.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:19.46,0:14:20.67,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Saturday nights...
Dialogue: 0,0:14:22.09,0:14:26.13,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Did your brother happen to meet with anyone on Saturday nights?
Dialogue: 0,0:14:26.51,0:14:27.67,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Yeah...
Dialogue: 0,0:14:27.67,0:14:32.35,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,He would often venture out on Saturday\Nnights and not return until morning.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:32.35,0:14:35.39,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,My brother's wife, who died the\Nyear before last, told me about it.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:36.39,0:14:42.90,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,She was worried he was using Saturday nights for an affair,\Nand would always call his pager to keep tabs on him.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:43.44,0:14:47.40,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,It seems my brother would grow angry as he called back.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:48.19,0:14:49.70,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,"I'm going to the Doctor's now!"
Dialogue: 0,0:14:49.70,0:14:50.78,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,"Quit nagging!"
Dialogue: 0,0:14:50.78,0:14:51.66,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Like that.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:52.37,0:14:53.83,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Could that doctor be...
Dialogue: 0,0:14:54.41,0:14:57.12,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,The first victim in the case, Doctor Boukawa!?
Dialogue: 0,0:14:57.50,0:14:58.33,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Yeah.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:58.33,0:15:02.46,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I told the police about it twenty years\Nago, and it seems they looked into it.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:03.46,0:15:08.17,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Apparently my brother's name wasn't on his patient list, right?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:08.17,0:15:10.09,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,That does seem to be the case, huh?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:18.10,0:15:20.06,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,What is it, Detective Takagi?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:20.06,0:15:21.60,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Did you come across something?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:21.60,0:15:22.85,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Nothing at all.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:24.27,0:15:25.65,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,And you, Ayumi{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-chan{\r} and Haibara?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:26.07,0:15:28.32,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Did either seem similar to the culprit?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:28.57,0:15:31.28,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I didn't notice any similarities.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:31.86,0:15:34.62,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,And I don't think it was the old lady.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:34.99,0:15:40.62,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Well, if they had been wearing a wig and synthetic\Nfacial hair when we passed by them earlier...
Dialogue: 0,0:15:41.04,0:15:42.75,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,It's possible our impression could change, isn't it?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:43.17,0:15:43.96,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,That's true.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:44.58,0:15:45.96,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Where are we headed next?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:46.38,0:15:48.63,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Ah, the last one is...
Dialogue: 0,0:15:48.63,0:15:53.09,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Related to the murder case that occurred\Nfive years after the cases twenty years ago.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:53.47,0:15:56.93,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,We'll be meeting Eika{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r}, who is the son\Nof the murdered lawyer, Nabei Susumu.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:06.77,0:16:09.82,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Eiki{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r} was just 10 years old at the time.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:09.82,0:16:13.28,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,He was sleeping in his room and was awoken by his father's moaning.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:14.16,0:16:18.08,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Between when the culprit left and his\Nmother returned home from shopping...
Dialogue: 0,0:16:18.08,0:16:20.62,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,He was too scared to even leave his room.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:21.58,0:16:25.96,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,His mother went into shock after seeing her\Nhusband's body, and ended up bedridden...
Dialogue: 0,0:16:26.38,0:16:32.13,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,She is still hospitalized to this day, and\NEiki{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r} continues to live alone in the house.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:32.76,0:16:35.22,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Enough is enough, Detective!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:35.39,0:16:38.26,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Have I not discussed this case with the police enough!?
Dialogue: 0,0:16:38.43,0:16:43.85,Character Card,,0,0,0,,{\fad(210,0)}Nabei Eiki (25)\NSon of Nabei Susumu
Dialogue: 0,0:16:38.68,0:16:41.14,Dialogue Top,,0,0,0,,With this deadline coming up...
Dialogue: 0,0:16:41.18,0:16:42.77,Dialogue Top,,0,0,0,,The news people are all over me!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:42.81,0:16:43.85,Dialogue Top,,0,0,0,,I'm tired of this shit!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:44.48,0:16:48.11,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,So what if this criminal that killed my father got someone else!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:48.11,0:16:49.27,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,How does that concern me!?
Dialogue: 0,0:16:50.44,0:16:51.57,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Well...
Dialogue: 0,0:16:52.03,0:16:55.70,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,We just want to know if your father was\Nacquainted with this man, Hiramune{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r}...
Dialogue: 0,0:16:56.53,0:16:57.41,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Who knows!?
Dialogue: 0,0:16:57.41,0:16:58.20,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Idiot!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:58.62,0:16:59.74,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Idiot?
Dialogue: 0,0:17:05.17,0:17:08.59,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,It seems he wasn't always like this.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:08.59,0:17:09.46,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Really?
Dialogue: 0,0:17:09.63,0:17:10.63,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Yeah.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:10.63,0:17:14.13,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,According to the inspector, when the boy\Nwas questioned about the incident...
Dialogue: 0,0:17:14.13,0:17:17.55,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,He claimed that, before the murder, his\Nfather had said something strange.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:18.22,0:17:22.02,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,It seems every time he remembered something, he\Nwould come to the police to report it immediately.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:22.97,0:17:24.31,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Something strange?
Dialogue: 0,0:17:24.81,0:17:30.02,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,He usually slept until noon on Sundays, and it seems\Nhe was mumbling something after waking up...
Dialogue: 0,0:17:30.48,0:17:33.82,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,"Had some parents run over last night as well, too bad."
Dialogue: 0,0:17:33.82,0:17:34.40,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Like that.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:35.03,0:17:38.32,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Someone's parents were probably run over by a car.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:38.32,0:17:39.45,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I see!
Dialogue: 0,0:17:39.45,0:17:41.62,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,It's because he was a lawyer.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:41.62,0:17:45.08,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,He probably decided to defend the ones\Nresponsible or the victims involved.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:45.46,0:17:46.41,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,And?
Dialogue: 0,0:17:46.41,0:17:48.92,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Why is that considered strange?
Dialogue: 0,0:17:48.92,0:17:53.00,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,The murder victim, Nabei{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r}, specialized in corporate cases.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:53.00,0:17:55.76,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,It appears he never took on a traffic case.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:57.26,0:17:58.18,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Then, why?
Dialogue: 0,0:17:58.64,0:18:03.18,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,It seems Eiki{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r} found it strange and didn't\Nunderstand it either, so he reported it to the police.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:05.27,0:18:06.60,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Crybaby...
Dialogue: 0,0:18:07.39,0:18:09.10,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Going to the Doctor's...
Dialogue: 0,0:18:09.94,0:18:12.11,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,And parents being run over, huh?
Dialogue: 0,0:18:13.36,0:18:14.28,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I see.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:17.20,0:18:18.57,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I finally get it...
Dialogue: 0,0:18:19.24,0:18:21.53,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,The connection between the four victims.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:26.08,0:18:26.96,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Mahjong?
Dialogue: 0,0:18:27.71,0:18:31.84,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,The connection between the four serial murder victims...
Dialogue: 0,0:18:31.84,0:18:33.46,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,It's really just mahjong?
Dialogue: 0,0:18:33.80,0:18:37.38,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Hiramune{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r} said it when he was on the talk show, right?
Dialogue: 0,0:18:38.09,0:18:42.68,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,It was when he said, "He'll keep disposing of his\Nsafe tiles, just waiting for this round to end."
Dialogue: 0,0:18:43.39,0:18:46.39,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,That's all mahjong terminology, right?
Dialogue: 0,0:18:46.72,0:18:49.06,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Hiramune{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r} must have truly liked mahjong.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:50.15,0:18:52.31,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,That may be true, but...
Dialogue: 0,0:18:52.31,0:18:53.40,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,What about the other three?
Dialogue: 0,0:18:53.98,0:18:57.57,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,The first victim that was killed, the doctor, Boukawa{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r}...
Dialogue: 0,0:18:57.57,0:19:00.32,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,He came home drunk one Saturday night...
Dialogue: 0,0:19:00.32,0:19:04.24,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,And apparently said, "Wouldn't stop with the\N'crybaby, crybaby,' making me out to be an idiot"
Dialogue: 0,0:19:04.66,0:19:07.33,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,As for the associate professor of\Nscience and engineering, Mugita{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r}...
Dialogue: 0,0:19:07.33,0:19:11.67,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Also on Saturday nights, his wife would call\Nhis pager, and when he called back...
Dialogue: 0,0:19:12.21,0:19:15.75,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,"I'm going to the Doctor's now, stop nagging," he said angrily.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:16.30,0:19:20.51,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,The lawyer who was killed five years\Nlater, Nabei{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r}, got up one Sunday...
Dialogue: 0,0:19:20.68,0:19:21.84,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,And the first thing he said...
Dialogue: 0,0:19:21.84,0:19:26.18,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Was something like,"Had some parents run\Nover last night as well, too bad," right?
Dialogue: 0,0:19:26.47,0:19:31.44,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,The crybaby Boukawa{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r} mentioned was actually\Nmisheard for what's known as opening doors in mahjong.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:31.81,0:19:33.35,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Why would he want to cry?
Dialogue: 0,0:19:33.69,0:19:35.40,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Isn't mahjong just a game?
Dialogue: 0,0:19:35.77,0:19:38.57,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,It's when you try to hurry and win early...
Dialogue: 0,0:19:38.57,0:19:43.99,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,By collecting tiles discarded by other\Nplayers, to form groups of 3's and 4's.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:43.99,0:19:45.16,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,That's opening doors.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:45.78,0:19:46.70,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Then...
Dialogue: 0,0:19:46.70,0:19:49.66,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,"Had some parents run over last night as well, too bad" means...
Dialogue: 0,0:19:50.12,0:19:53.67,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,It could have been, "Had oya ni run over last night as well, too bad."
Dialogue: 0,0:19:54.17,0:19:56.67,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,His son Eiki{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r} could have misheard that, right?
Dialogue: 0,0:19:57.09,0:20:01.67,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,The parent in mahjong refers to the dealer,\Nwho can capitalize for extra points.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:01.67,0:20:06.26,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,To personally be run over is to be overtaken by\Nsomeone who has more points, thereby losing.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:06.51,0:20:07.31,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,So...
Dialogue: 0,0:20:07.47,0:20:12.02,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,What he really meant was, "Had the dealer\Nrun me over last night as well, too bad."
Dialogue: 0,0:20:12.39,0:20:16.69,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,But, what about Mugita{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r} saying, "I'm going to the Doctor's now"?
Dialogue: 0,0:20:18.15,0:20:19.48,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,That was probably...
Dialogue: 0,0:20:19.86,0:20:22.86,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,"I'm listening to the tiles now, stop nagging," or...
Dialogue: 0,0:20:22.86,0:20:25.16,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Something like that.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:25.37,0:20:27.20,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,It's true!
Dialogue: 0,0:20:27.20,0:20:29.79,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,It does sound like "going to the Doctor's."
Dialogue: 0,0:20:29.79,0:20:32.58,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,But what does that mean, "listening to the tiles"?
Dialogue: 0,0:20:33.16,0:20:37.09,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,When you're just one tile away from a\Nwin, it's called "listening to the tiles."
Dialogue: 0,0:20:37.59,0:20:40.26,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,"One more" tile is what you need.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:40.59,0:20:46.01,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,That's why he angrily said, "I'm listening to the tiles, stop nagging."
Dialogue: 0,0:20:46.39,0:20:47.30,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Well...
Dialogue: 0,0:20:47.30,0:20:53.73,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Since everything they said involved mahjong terminology,\Nit shouldn't be surprising that non-players misheard them.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:54.48,0:20:55.27,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,That's true...
Dialogue: 0,0:20:56.06,0:21:00.69,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Those who heard these statements were\NBoukawa{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r} and Mugita{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r}'s wives...
Dialogue: 0,0:21:00.69,0:21:04.32,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,As well as Nabei{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r}'s son, Eiki{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r}, who was still a child.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:05.28,0:21:09.66,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,What the suspect said when Eiki{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r} was\Na child was also related to mahjong.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:09.99,0:21:10.95,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,What the suspect said?
Dialogue: 0,0:21:11.49,0:21:16.37,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,After the suspect killed his father and was\Non his way out, Eiki{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r} apparently heard...
Dialogue: 0,0:21:17.08,0:21:18.71,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,"Don't think I'm cruel."
Dialogue: 0,0:21:18.71,0:21:20.30,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,"I'm having you pay your dues."
Dialogue: 0,0:21:20.71,0:21:24.47,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,"Because you had to talk like that, I had to ready my hand."
Dialogue: 0,0:21:24.76,0:21:28.47,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,"And as a result, I ended up with this long scar from the cops."
Dialogue: 0,0:21:28.68,0:21:29.39,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,That's it.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:30.18,0:21:33.85,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Paying your dues and readying your hand are both part of mahjong.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:34.52,0:21:35.44,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,And?
Dialogue: 0,0:21:35.94,0:21:37.31,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,What do we do now?
Dialogue: 0,0:21:37.90,0:21:38.98,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Do you have to ask?
Dialogue: 0,0:21:39.61,0:21:44.74,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,The probability of those four meeting for\Nmahjong on Saturday nights is high.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:45.24,0:21:49.24,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Now is the time to narrow our search to the mahjong parlors...
Dialogue: 0,0:21:49.24,0:21:52.74,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,That those four could have accessed easily from their homes and jobs.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:53.24,0:21:59.71,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,When it comes to mahjong parlors, even complete strangers\Nwill play together, with no mind for differences in age.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:01.79,0:22:02.88,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,All right!
Dialogue: 0,0:22:03.30,0:22:05.13,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Detective Boys...
Dialogue: 0,0:22:05.13,0:22:07.18,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Let's go!
Dialogue: 0,0:22:08.55,0:22:10.76,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,For you all, is the time all right?
Dialogue: 0,0:22:11.60,0:22:12.97,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,It's already 9:00.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:13.47,0:22:14.89,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Don't worry.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:14.89,0:22:17.69,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,We told our moms we would be staying at the Professor's tonight!
Dialogue: 0,0:22:18.14,0:22:19.73,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,"No problem."
Dialogue: 0,0:22:20.06,0:22:21.36,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Oh, really...
Dialogue: 0,0:22:23.69,0:22:25.69,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,All right, let's do this!
Dialogue: 0,0:22:25.69,0:22:26.99,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Yeah!
Dialogue: 0,0:22:32.49,0:22:34.54,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Just wait, Whistling Man...
Dialogue: 0,0:22:34.87,0:22:38.29,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I'll uncover your true face without a doubt.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:00.37,0:24:01.71,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,It's our man on the line!
Dialogue: 0,0:24:02.04,0:24:04.46,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Take absolute caution!
Dialogue: 0,0:24:05.00,0:24:08.38,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,When it comes to hostages, I guess it'll just be me, huh?
Dialogue: 0,0:24:30.82,0:24:33.15,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Next Conan's Hint
Dialogue: 0,0:24:33.20,0:24:34.91,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Mouse
Dialogue: 0,0:24:34.95,0:24:36.87,Dialogue Top,,0,0,0,,Why is it called a mouse?
Dialogue: 0,0:24:36.91,0:24:38.45,Dialogue Top,,0,0,0,,You'll know next week!
Dialogue: 0,0:24:38.45,0:24:39.91,Dialogue Top,,0,0,0,,Genta's talking strangely...
